                <h1>Exploring Thomas Jefferson's Early Life and Influences</h1>
                <p>Thomas Jefferson was born on April 13, 1743, in Colonial Virginia. Raised in a wealthy plantation family, he received an extensive education at the College of William & Mary. Jefferson developed interests in law, philosophy, and the arts. His early experiences on his estate, Monticello, shaped his views on government and human rights, laying the foundation for his future role as a Founding Father.</p>
